  "prompt": "Did any Russian officials attend Shirom Peres funeral?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, there are no widely reported instances of high-ranking Russian officials attending Shimon Peres's funeral. Shimon Peres, the former President and Prime Minister of Israel, passed away on September 28, 2016, and his state funeral on September 30, 2016, in Caesarea was attended by numerous international dignitaries, including leaders from the United States, United Kingdom, Germany, and other nations. \n\nWhile it's possible that lower-level officials or representatives from Russia may have attended without significant media coverage, there is no prominent documentation or reports indicating that senior Russian officials, such as President Vladimir Putin or Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov, were present at the funeral. \n\nDiplomatic relations and state funerals typically attract attendance from leaders with strong bilateral ties, and the absence of Russian high-ranking officials suggests that they may not have been present. However, for the most accurate and detailed information, consulting official records or statements from the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs around the time of the funeral could provide further clarity.",
